    <info_history><![CDATA[
v1.12 - Tim Shadow July 21, 2013
-Fixed "Armor Mastery" mythic ability to remove the ACP correctly.
-Fixed "Sacred Boons"  to correctly calculates its bonus as 2x Mthyic Tier and it now correctly affects the domain powers.
    
v1.11 - Tim Shadow May 5, 2013
-Fixed old file that got into the package and did raise dead on the "incorrect attribute increase" vermin monster.
-Also fixed the incorrect version number of 1.09 that was showing for v1.10. It now correctly shows v1.11.

v1.10 - Tim Shadow May 5, 2013
-Fixed "cMaPGrePow" "Greater Power" to not throw error when the update is turned on.
-Fix to the "Mythic Magic" procedure to actually find ALL classes. This will prevent incorrect notice of the mythic spells not valid error message some classes where getting.

v1.9 - Tim Shadow March 23, 2013
-Fixed issue where the Attribute increase every 4 levels was sometimes giving an error message about having too many.

V1.8 - Tim Shadow
-Removed the "Source" on the Mythic Playtest Mechanic. This preventst the odd error on a character load about the mechanic not being live.
-Found a few strange cases where a Feat/Trait picked up the Mythic Tiers as levels still causing some totals to be off. These tags have been fixed to prevent the Teir from being seen as a class or Hit Dice.

V1.7 - Tim Shadow December 22, 2012
-Added in Jason Bulmahn forum post of updated rules from 12/21/12. This is a new source that you have to turn on in the "Configure Your Hero" window. This way groups can decide to use these changes or not as they see fit.
http://paizo.com/threads/rzs2paun?Mythic-Adventures-Update-122112
-The "Mythic" template will add a 2nd tab called "Mythic Abilties" that allows one to choose Mythic Path abilities. I am leaving it up to the DM to figure out the correct abilities to select as some path abilities don't make sense for Monsters.
-Redid the sources a little to add in the new "Update 12/21/2012" rule changes.
-Added a warning message and note for the "Dual Focus" feat that it should not be taken or swapped out if you are now using the 12/21/2012 rule updates.
-New "Mythic Power" adjusment added that lets you up/down the number of mythic power points per day your character has.

V1.6 - Tim Shadow December 2, 2012
-Fixed the skill point calculation for humans that where still off.
-Known Issue - Found a strange issue I can't currently fix.  If in the "Configure Your Hero" window for "HP Options" you have checked "Average HPs at New Levels" and then add a Mythic Tier you will gain an extra hit point.  Current work around is to "uncheck" this option then add your Mythic Tier and then you can turn it back on.

V1.5 - Tim Shadow December 1, 2012
-Fixed the skill point calculation so most likely you will see you have some additional skills to spend. This is not correct.
-If you have multiple Paths the "Bonus Hit Point" class abilities will give an option to Enable/Disable so that you can tell HL which is the correct one to use.  This gives the most flexability and leave it up to each group/gamer.
    
V1.4 - Tim Shadow November 27, 2012
-Emergency fix of Mythic Power die size was always showing 2d8 instead of the correct amount at tier 1.

V1.3 - Tim Shadow November 27, 2012
-Finished scripting all Path abilities. This includes even just some helper text when the bonus is a situational modifier.

V1.2 - Tim Shadow November 24, 2012
-Added templates: Invincible and Savage.
-Fixed some calculations on the Divine/Arcane templates to correctly go to MR2 with enough Hit Dice.
-Mythic Tier will now give a error message if no Path as been taken. This should help remind gamers new to this addon what they need to do. Thanks "Lord Magus" for this suggestion.
-Improved the "Flaws" to be fully scripted and have more accurate choices for "Material Weakness".
-Scripted up the Unversial Path Abilities to have activations now that affect your character.

V1.1 - Tim Shadow November 23, 2012
-Added in "Mythic Tier" header XML that Mathias was nice to provide. This will cause the Paths to correctly display under the "Mythic Tier" class now.    
-Tested against Pathfinder v7.4.

November 14, 2012 - Tim Shadow
-Created New to hold the Frame Work and mechanics required for the Mythic Playtest.]]></info_history>
